    "narrative": "Today\u2019s lineup is anchored by **Tyler Freeman** (72.83) and **Bryson Stott** (68.59), who represent our strongest statistical plays. **Tyler Freeman** benefits from a high-upside matchup against a regressing Cristian Javier; his lead-off spot, combined with an elite park factor and a favorable SB environment, makes him our anchor. Similarly, **Bryson Stott** draws a targetable matchup against Tyler Mahle, and despite a slight penalty for catcher arm strength, his dynamic platoon advantage pushes him toward the elite tier of today's scoring. **Lawrence Butler** (66.38) and **Masyn Winn** (64.64) also project well, with **Lawrence Butler** maximizing a +13% platoon boost against Will Warren, and **Masyn Winn** capitalizing on the generous 4.83 xERA of Miles Mikolas.\n\nWe are forced to navigate significant risk with **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (56.26), who falls into the marginal bucket today due to a brutal matchup against Cole Ragans (2.52 xERA). Despite the 19% handicap from the opponent's skill, his floor remains high enough to warrant inclusion over the bench. The most difficult bench decision was bypassing **Will Smith** (54.87). While his xwOBA profile remains strong, the optimizer prioritized the higher-ceiling platoon matchups of **Gavin Sheets** and **Jeremiah Jackson**. **Will Smith** was ultimately squeezed out by the difficulty of the matchup against Dylan Cease, which dragged his score just below the threshold for our current active roster.\n\nManagement should monitor the lineups for **Cal Raleigh**, **Jonathan Aranda**, and **Gleyber Torres**, as all remain \"Lineup Pending.\" **Gleyber Torres** in particular carries a volatile profile today; while a 5% wind boost helps, his heavy reliance on platoon splits makes his 55.55 score sensitive to any mid-day lineup adjustments. With **Luis Arraez**, **Matt Chapman**, and **Daulton Varsho** all sitting on the bench with scores in the low 50s, we have sufficient depth if any of the projected starters are scratched. We are keeping **Brendan Donovan**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Wenceel Perez**, and **Drew Gilbert** in reserve to maintain maximum flexibility should weather or late scratches force a pivot.",
